column5: My first attempt at posting a vid went like hell it took 4 hours and lost my theme music on the way there!!  :wallbash:  I dunno what happened....  I was accompanied by "Eric Johnson's Cliffs of Dover" pretty good tune... anyway here it is.   RFS    http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Rq78Q
EVEN THAT DIDN'T WORK!!!!  :wallbash:   I'll be back....

Cliff's of Dover is an awesome tune!  I learned to play it...well up to the insanely fast and smooth part in the last part of the song...LOL.  I can help with the video if you need it...just let me know ok?

Neat video. Never been on the river. Thanks for the ride!  Hey Randy you told me earlier you were helping your kids with homework. Maybe you should get them to help you with this! Ha.  I'm really picking on you tonight!
Eh! Bernie...  I'll have the guys in North Bay give you a hard time tomorrow.  :clapping:
Fine job Randy your boat seems to go pretty fast.  Where was that taken.
Pas loin de chez nous 30 minutes.. Marten River, Ontario ...   Lac Turcotte  Not to far away 30 munites or so    Turcotte Lake..... Marten River,Ontario     RFS
Ah I have been down the Martin River in a canoe when I was a kid
aye est-ce que c'était l'esturgeon que tu pêchais?  Le lien n'y arrive pas mon grand!  T'as ti essayé photobucket?  Chcapotte icite!

I had the same problem with posting my recent vacation pics. (user legacey69)  Spent a while compiling the pictures and sound. Uploaded it and 24 hours later received an email that it contained copywritten music. The band was Squirrel Nut Zippers if anyone has heard of them.....too bad, it fit perfectly.  First I get banned by Metalica on Napster, now them....I can't win!  I guess I'll have to record some  I've since heard Youtube and the music industry are in a battle and they will now remove your audio.  Good luck.  Paul
